What you will learn:

Configuration of 'require.js' is done in the 'require.config' section.

How to use this sample:

1. Compare this code sample with the previous code sample.

2. Notice te inclusion of 'require.config' in the 'main.js' file.

3. In your editor, e.g., NetBeans IDE, explore the options within the require.config section.

4. Be aware that this structure is something you'll see in all Oracle JET applications.